						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the outer <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarman</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhº Sundara-pāṇḍyadēva (II): Year 13+1 = 1289-90 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that from the above-mentioned year in the reign of the king, each trader, each loom of a weaver, each loom of <hi rend="italic">Śāliyar,</hi> and each oil-monger of Tirukkachchūr should pay annually 6 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> and of the total income thus derived one half should go to the <hi rend="italic">Śrībhaṇḍāra</hi> (of the temple).</p>						

